The operating system function of security is very important. This function protects users from outside threats. This security function is key to guarding data on a computer system.
Device Controllers are a function of the operating system that is essential. Basically, all devices connected to a computer are controlled by the operating system. Otherwise, how would the computer allow input through the keyboard, mouse, microphone, etc...?
Operating Systems provide a User-Interface. This function provides two options, a graphic-line interface or a command-line interface. The graphic-line interface is the more common, user-friendly interface of the two.
